{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the order said, you-- you're not to allow any of the inmates to fall into the hands of Allied troops.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, how could they help it?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they were frantic, so they were moving people around like crazy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's how that train came in from Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Buchenwald commander-- Buchenwald was overrun by Patton's 3rd Army before we took Dachau, about a week or so before.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the commandant of Buchenwald moved a bunch of people, tried to get rid of a bunch.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But how could they get rid of 1,000 people?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They couldn't do it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Dachau, the commandant went crazy and he started marching-- we don't know how many thousand, but anywhere from 3,000 to 5,000 that were there-- he started marching them towards Austria.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And most of them died.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were policing up bodies for miles around and it turned out we had something like 9,000 dead bodies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So how-- how-- how do you handle that many dead?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You can't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we made the citizens of Dachau help with the burial.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we just took bulldozers and dug deep trenches and tried to identify people with numbers or whatever we could, any way to identify them-- many you could not identify-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and buried them in mass burials.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the-- the people of Dachau was made to witness and to help out with that, you see.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What was their reaction to that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, many of them were cried and saying they-- well, they didn't know-- they weren't part of it, they didn't know anything about it, which is to a great extent true.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
